<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - WorkStar&#8482; Series Starting March 2007 - REMOVE AND INSTALL
        PROCEDURES - Headlight Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Headlight Assembly</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Assembly - Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Removal of the right side headlight assembly is shown in this procedure. The left side
                        headlight assembly must be removed in the same manner after first removing the upper splash
                        panel.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0901419" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901419.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Headlight Assembly Attaching Hardware</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the headlight harness connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not allow the headlight assembly to fall out of the hood while removing the mounting
                        hardware.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four nuts and one bolt from the headlight assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901418" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901418.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Headlight Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the headlight assembly from the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Assembly - Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Installation of the right side headlight assembly is shown in this procedure. The left side
                        headlight assembly must be installed in the same manner. The upper splash panel may then be
                        installed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the headlight assembly in the hood opening (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901418">Figure 39, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure with four nuts and one bolt (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901419">Figure 38, Items 1 and 3</hotlnk>). Torque nuts to 11 to 13 lbf-ft. (15 to
                    18 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the headlight harness connector (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901419">Figure 38, Item 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Bulb - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0901420" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901420.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Headlight Bulb Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT BEZEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RETAINER RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT BULB</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT BULB SOCKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. RETAINER RING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. BEZEL SCREW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four bezel screws from the headlight bezel and remove the headlight bezel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three retainer ring screws from the retainer ring and remove the retainer ring.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unplug the headlight bulb from the headlight bulb socket and remove the headlight bulb
                    from the headlight housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Bulb - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the headlight bulb in the headlight housing, plug the headlight bulb into the
                    headlight bulb socket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901420">Figure 40, Items 3, 4, and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the retainer ring holes with the headlight housing holes and install the three
                    retainer ring screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901420">Figure 40, Items 2, 5, and 6</hotlnk>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the headlight bezel holes with the headlight housing holes and install the four
                    bezel screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901420">Figure 40, Items 1, 5, and 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Adjustment</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The headlight adjustment is made with the vehicle level and the headlights on.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0901422" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901422.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Headlight Adjustment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT BEZEL ACCESS HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. VERTICAL ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HORIZONTAL ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the vertical and horizontal adjustment screws just inside the headlight bezel
                    access holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the use of a Phillips head screwdriver, adjust the headlight beam vertically or
                    horizontally by turning the vertical or horizontal adjusting screws clockwise or counterclockwise as
                    needed.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Turn Signal Bulb - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0901421" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901421.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Turn Signal Bulb</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TURN SIGNAL BULB</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TURN SIGNAL BULB SOCKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the socket cover counterclockwise and remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the turn signal bulb socket counterclockwise and remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turn signal bulb from the turn signal bulb socket.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Turn Signal Bulb - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the turn signal bulb in the turn signal bulb socket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901421">Figure 42, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the turn signal bulb in the proper position in the headlight assembly and turn
                    clockwise to lock it in position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the socket cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901421">Figure 42, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
